mrmc.core

Class DBRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • mrmc.core.DBRecord

  • public class DBRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    The contents of an .omrmc file. Summary info from a reader study. This class includes all the information on one study. it also includes all the formulas to convert one decomposition to the other. The conversion formulas are based on Gallas BD, Bandos A, Samuelson F, Wagner RF. A Framework for random-effects ROC analsysis: Biases with the Bootstrap and other variance estimatorsï¿½, Commun Stat A-Theory 38(15), 2586-2603 (2009).
    Important fields
    ----recordDesc
    ----recordTitle
    ----filename
    ----Task

    makeTMatrices(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) takes study data (InputFile.keyedData, InputFile.truthVals) and creates data for CovMRMC
    --t-matrices: reader scores
    ----t0_modAA, t0_modAB, t0_modBB: signal-absent scores [Nnormal ][Nreader][2 modalities]
    ----t1_modAA, t1_modAB, t1_modBB: signal-present scores [Ndisease][Nreader][2 modalities]
    --d-matrices: study design
    ----d0_modAA, d0_modAB, d0_modBB: signal absent scores [Nnormal ][Nreader][2 modalities]
    ----d1_modAA, d1_modAB, d1_modBB: signal present scores [Ndisease][Nreader][2 modalities]
    CALLED BY: RawStudyCard.varAnalysisListener

    calculateCovMRMC(java.lang.Integer)
    ----BDG, BDGbiased, BDGcoeff, [AA, BB, AB, A+B-2AB], [4][8] arrays
    ----
    ----AUCs, [Nreader][2] array
    ----AUCsReaderAvg, [2] array
    ----totalVar based on the current study

    generateDecompositions()
    ----BCK, BCKbias, BCKcoeff, [4][7] arrays
    ----If fully-crossed data,
    --------DBM, DBMbias, DBMcoeff [4][6] arrays:
    --------OR, ORbias, ORcoeff, [4][6] arrays:
    --------MS, MSbias, MScoeff, [4][6] arrays:

    Author:
    Xin He, Ph.D,, Brandon D. Gallas, Ph.D, Rohan Pathare

      • makeTMatrices

        public void makeTMatrices(java.lang.String modA,
                 java.lang.String modB)
        Takes study data (InputFile.keyedData, InputFile.keyedData) and creates data for CovMRMC
        --t-matrices: reader scores
        ----t0_modAA, t0_modAB, t0_modBB: signal-absent scores [Nnormal ][Nreader][2 modalities]
        ----t1_modAA, t1_modAB, t1_modBB: signal-present scores [Ndisease][Nreader][2 modalities]
        --d-matrices: study design
        ----d0_modAA, d0_modAB, d0_modBB: signal absent scores [Nnormal ][Nreader][2 modalities]
        ----d1_modAA, d1_modAB, d1_modBB: signal present scores [Ndisease][Nreader][2 modalities]
        Parameters:
        modA - Modality to be used as mod 0
        modB - Modality to be used as mod 1
